							<section id="content-section-1" ><div class="section-container container"><div class="gdlr-item gdlr-content-item" ><h3><img class="alignleft  wp-image-1263" src="http://www.business-writers.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/huwb.jpg" alt="huwb" width="85" height="85" /></h3>
<h4>My passion is helping clients develop conversations that engage people and inspire change. I am fascinated by dynamic individuals and the companies they help create, and enjoy uncovering their stories. I&#8217;m also interested in exploring new business ideas and <a href="http://www.norfolknetwork.com/fiction-reality-will-artificial-intelligence-change-world/">advances in technology</a>.</h4>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em><span style="color: #ef8737;">“Huw is an expert at summarising, clarifying and finding the right context for an article. He can really dig into your business and write a clear story which touches base.”<br /></span></em><em><span style="color: #ef8737;">&#8211; People &amp; Organisation Manager at leading global consultancy.</span></em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>I&#8217;ve had the pleasure of developing many <a href="https://www.theconsultanthub.com/christian-barnes-consultant-15315.html">creative partnerships</a> over the past 16 years with clients who value the written word. As well as writing copy for them, I&#8217;ve helped them use social media to engage with their customers and build their businesses. If you share my passion and would like me to support your team&#8217;s strategic communications, please get in touch.</p>
<p>Over the last 25-years in international marketing, I&#8217;ve created a range of communications for customers, employees and investors. Clients have included Aon, HSBC Investment Banking, AkzoNobel, SSAFA, Oxford GlycoScience and Reuters. Now you can draw on my knowledge and experience to help you achieve your marketing and business objectives.</p>
<p>Outside work, I use social media and speaking engagements to champion innovation and culture in East Anglia. My aim is to <a title="#VisitNorfolk #VisitNorwich Now" href="https://paper.li/HuwSayer/1360356883" target="_blank" rel="noopener">encourage more people to visit our region</a> and <a title="Putting Norwich on the UK's tech map." href="http://www.edp24.co.uk/business/norwich_ready_to_join_a_list_of_technology_centres_1_3715104" target="_blank" rel="noopener">more businesses to invest</a> here. The <strong><span style="color: #ef8737;">Eastern Daily Press</span></strong> called me <a href="http://www.eveningnews24.co.uk/news/the_norfolk_and_suffolk_twit_list_2014_1_3168836">“one of the top 20 tweeters in the region.”</a> While the <strong><span style="color: #ef8737;">EDP Norfolk Magazine</span></strong> called me <a title="Championing local food &amp; drink." href="http://www.norfolkmag.co.uk/people/we_are_the_champions_1_3784579" target="_blank" rel="noopener">“a great Norfolk online ambassador.”</a></p>
<p>In November 2017 I joined the <a href="https://norfolkchamber.co.uk/corporate/chamber-board/huw-sayer">board of the Norfolk Chamber of Commerce</a> as a non-executive director. I look forward supporting our business community and ensuring the Chamber stays relevant to its members. Please let me know if there are any issues you would like to discuss.</p>
</div><div class="clear"></div><div class="gdlr-stunning-text-ux gdlr-ux"><div class="gdlr-item gdlr-stunning-text-item gdlr-button-on type-normal with-padding with-border" ><h2 class="stunning-text-title">You are welcome to contact Huw Sayer by phone, email or LinkedIn.</h2><div class="stunning-text-caption"><p>T: +44 (0) 20 7193 4806</p>
<p><a style="text-decoration: none;" href="https://uk.linkedin.com/pub/huw-sayer/4/188/671"><span style="font: 80% Arial,sans-serif; color: #0783b6;"><img style="vertical-align: middle;" src="https://static.licdn.com/scds/common/u/img/webpromo/btn_in_20x15.png" alt="View Huw Sayer's LinkedIn profile" width="20" height="15" border="0" /> View Huw Sayer&#8217;s profile</span></a></p>
</div><a class="stunning-text-button gdlr-button with-border" href="mailto:huw@business-writers.co.uk">Email</a></div></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="gdlr-item-title-wrapper  pos-left"><h3 class="gdlr-item-title gdlr-skin-title gdlr-skin-border">Huw Sayer presenting #DynamicEast on Mustard TV</h3><div class="gdlr-item-caption gdlr-skin-info">Exploring the dynamic business sectors of Norfolk and Suffolk - October 2016.</div><div class="clear"></div></div><div class="gdlr-item gdlr-content-item" ><p>When <a href="http://www.mustardtv.co.uk/">Mustard TV</a> invited Huw to share his passion for enterprise in the East of England with a wider audience, he leapt at the chance. Working with the producer and camera crew, Huw helped create six programmes exploring the dynamic business communities in Norfolk and Suffolk. As well as drafting the scripts, Huw conducted the interviews and (for the first time) presented the series. </p>
<p>Now you can watch all six programmes on YouTube &#8211; see the link below.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><em><span style="color: #ef8737;">If you&#8217;d like Huw to present your corporate video or do any voice-over work, please get in touch.</span></em></p>
</blockquote>
</div><div class="clear"></div><div class="gdlr-video-item gdlr-item"  ><iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/CqpcTurkISk?wmode=transparent" width="620" height="348" ></iframe></div><div class="clear"></div></div></section>			<div class="main-content-container container gdlr-item-start-content">
